    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "To complete @Haroenv's answer, the second option can be emulated using a first empty query. In order to do this you need to [create a custom widget](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/guides/custom-widget.html).\r\n\r\nDuring the init, you should use the helper to make a new query using [searchOnce](https://community.algolia.com/algoliasearch-helper-js/reference.html#AlgoliaSearchHelper#searchOnce) and with the answer build your menu items. The facet values that you retrieve then can be used for filtering, with [helper.toggleFacetRefinement](https://community.algolia.com/algoliasearch-helper-js/reference.html#AlgoliaSearchHelper#toggleFacetRefinement).\r\n\r\nThe idea is that since you want a static menu, you shouldn't need to rerender anything afterwards.\r\n\r\nAs a side note, for implementation issues, we recommend using [stackoverflow](https://stackoverflow.com/tags/instantsearch.js/) or our [community forum](https://discourse.algolia.com/). This helps keep the issues for bugs or feature proposals, which really helps us :)",
